title: Hailey Baldwin heads to Kanye West's Yeezy 5 show
text:
She has been best friends with Kendall Jenner for two years, so it's no wonder Hailey Baldwin was seen heading to Kanye West's Yeezy 5 show in New York City on Wednesday.
The ex-girlfriend of Justin Bieber made a splash in her sexy outfit.
The 20-year-old Express model's sighting comes just after West's wife Kim Kardashian was spotted in all burgundy as she headed to the spectacle to meet up with sister Kylie Jenner.
The catwalk queen! Hailey Baldwin was all legs in her winter white outfit as she headed to Yeezy 5 in NYC on Wednesday
Her outfit was hard to grasp as the Tommy Hilfiger catwalker wore a sweatshirt tucked into a skirt over what looked to be a pair of shorts.
The design is most likely by West.
The star looked like she had just visited a tanning salon as her gams were golden.
Leggy lady: The star looked like she had just visited a tanning salon as her pins were golden
Model behaviour: Hailey wore her blonde locks scraped off her face in a sleek high ponytail and accentuated her striking looks with bronze make-up
Girls' day out: Hailey cosied up to musician Teyana Taylor inside the Yeezy show
Sporty: Her outfit was hard to grasp as the Tommy Hilfiger catwalker wore a sweatshirt tucked into a skirt over what looked to be a pair of shorts
Baldwin also wore silver platform heels that had thick ankle straps. In the cover girl's hand was a beige backpack and a water bottle.
A choker that was studded added a nice touch.
Guests descended on Pier 59 in Manhattan as they eagerly awaited the unveiling of Kanye's latest collection.
Mood? LOL: A choker that was studded added a nice touch
New pal? Here the daughter of actor Stephen Baldwin is seen with La La Anthony, 37
All in a line: The show kicked-off around 3pm ET with images of models projected onto a screen at the center of the runway, Vogue reports
With the chief: As with previous Yeezy shows Kim had a front row seat next to Vogue editor-in-chief Anna Wintour
The show kicked-off around 3pm ET with images of models projected onto a screen at the center of the runway, Vogue reports.
The venue was completely pitch black with attendees having to find their way to their seat using the light of their phones.
As with previous Yeezy shows Kim had a front row seat next to Vogue editor-in-chief Anna Wintour.
More famous faces: Kardashian was seen with Kylie Jenner and a pal
Kim looked to be very active at the show as she took photos with many supporters.
Kylie showed up with Tyga. She looked pretty in a cream outfit.
And one fan managed to get a photo of both Kim and Kanye after the show.
More supporters: The E! queen shared this image on Snapchat
